<div id="review_1185208220" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1185208220" />
    <a title="Puja" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6196787-puja"><img alt="Puja" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1453228949p2/6196787.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1185208220?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Puja" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Puja" href="/user/show/6196787-puja">Puja</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" " href="/book/show/23595546-tears-and-laughter">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6196787-puja?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1185208220" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10562586995956036089">Gibran&apos;s writings are lyrical, beautiful and deeply alluring in a mystical, spiritual, and magical way. As a non-believer, I should have found some of the spiritualism expressed in his poems and prose meaningless, however I was only moved by the depths of his emotion and love for the universe and all its beings. When he spoke about peace and harmony, it resonated with me. When he cried about poverty and misery, I felt the pain too. Through some of the short stories or passages in this book he ur</span>
  <span id="freeText10562586995956036089" style="display:none">Gibran's writings are lyrical, beautiful and deeply alluring in a mystical, spiritual, and magical way. As a non-believer, I should have found some of the spiritualism expressed in his poems and prose meaningless, however I was only moved by the depths of his emotion and love for the universe and all its beings. When he spoke about peace and harmony, it resonated with me. When he cried about poverty and misery, I felt the pain too. Through some of the short stories or passages in this book he urges the human kind to give up the destructive behavior and one cannot help but agree to him, given the way he so simply and beautifully conveys redemption and freedom. The last story, 'The Bride's Bed', apparently based on a true story, was particularly moving. Sad, that in today's day and age, similar stories are taking place. And we are clearly in need of more Gibrans to drive some sense into this mad world with his words of beauty and love.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10562586995956036089" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


