<div id="review_550991838" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/550991838" />
    <a title="Miss.dee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7308806-miss-dee"><img alt="Miss.dee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1356844482p2/7308806.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/550991838?book_show_action=true">Mar 03, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Miss.dee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Miss.dee" href="/user/show/7308806-miss-dee">Miss.dee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer550991838" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4336512098056855589">If you have ever loved and lost, either by death or other unbearable circumstance, if you have ever longed for your lover&apos;s touch, if you have ever seen the most awesome vision, if you have ever found happiness in your despair and tears, if you have ever seen death at your doorstep, and called for it, if you have ever wondered if anyone has ever felt these things you do, this book is certainly for you. There is a vast amount of symbology used cleverly and yet, obvious. I tried to dedicate a favo</span>
  <span id="freeText4336512098056855589" style="display:none">If you have ever loved and lost, either by death or other unbearable circumstance, if you have ever longed for your lover's touch, if you have ever seen the most awesome vision, if you have ever found happiness in your despair and tears, if you have ever seen death at your doorstep, and called for it, if you have ever wondered if anyone has ever felt these things you do, this book is certainly for you. There is a vast amount of symbology used cleverly and yet, obvious. I tried to dedicate a favorite passage and I could not. A well deserved space in my book shelf. This literary piece of art provides a "yardstick" for life, if you will... "I would not exchange the sorrows of my heart for the joys of the multitude.And I would not have the tears that sadness makes to flow from my every part turn into laughter. I would that my life remain a tear and a smile." Khalil has a way with imagery that is undefeated, highly recommended. There is a beauty within these lines that inspire the mind and reach down to the soul. This poet was a man, a philosopher that reaches beyond time into the future. Yet even today his words inspire and guide many a mind. A classic master.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4336512098056855589" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

